cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about facial action unit detection, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a novel framework that involves learning spatio-temporal relations and attention, which suggests that machine learning (cs.LG and cs.AI) may also be relevant categories. Additionally, the paper deals with video data, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the proposed method involves adaptively learning edge weights and regional attentions, which suggests that neural networks (cs.NE) may also be a relevant category.
